<br>
Hate, Fear, Disease, War.  Evil takes on many forms, as do those who follow the darker paths.  Evil, as well as beauty, is not skin deep, but rather exists in the soul, in the heart.  Appearances can be deceiving.  The palest skin can hide the blackest heart, and who is to say the Hate fueling the blades of a half elf is any less pure than the Hate in the veins of a Teir'dal?<br>
<br>
We of the Scythe come from many varied races and backgrounds, yet we all share one thing in common.  We walk in the Darkness.  We embrace the Darkness.  We are the Darkness.<br>
<br>
And no matter how our race should drive us apart, this common thread binds us tightly together.<br>
<br>
Are you of the Darkness?  Do you seek a family as you walk the path less traveled?  Let the Darkness envelope you, and visit us, the Scythe, the Harvesters of Darkness.<br>
<br>
((OOC:  We are a small, close knit <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>roleplaying</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> guild.  We are not a raiding guild, and to be honest, if you are looking for a guild where 50 members will be online at all times, we will not be a good fit.  What we can offer is a family where you will not be pressured to level, but encouraged to roleplay and develop your character.<br>
<br>
While we are an &quot;evil&quot; guild, roleplay is more important to us than pre-may 8th alignment restrictions.  This is not saying that we will accept the first wood elf druid that believes he is evil, but rather that your characters story is more important to us than your race.  <br>
<br>
Our Guild Hall is located in Shadowhaven, and can be visited here :<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness" target="top">Harvester Hall</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or in game by joining /harvesters.<br>
<br>
We request that you show your dedication to your character by reaching the 15th season before applying, however, feel free to visit the Hall at any time.))<br>
<br>
